      • edge

        public void edge(N srcNode,
                 D srcData,
                 E edge,
                 N tgtNode)
        Most general edge handler. In their default implementations, the following methods resort to calling this method:
        • treeEdge(Object, Object, Object, Object)
        • nontreeEdge(Object, Object, Object, Object, Object)
        Provided that the latter is not overwritten, the following methods resort to this method indirectly in their default implementation:
        • grayTarget(Object, Object, Object, Object, Object)
        • blackTarget(Object, Object, Object, Object, Object)
        Parameters:
        srcNode - the source node
        srcData - the data associated with the source node
        edge - the edge that is being processed
        tgtNode - the target node of this edge
